  "id": "MAL-2026-5423",
  "summary": "Malicious code in @nstrlabs/utils (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (84a4bcae5f6897112304920f60d6cbb6cbe880104db4ef1ff69be17fbb69b8ac)\nOn `npm install`, the package's preinstall lifecycle script runs index.js, which collects host identifiers (os.hostname(), os.userInfo().username, __dirname, process.cwd()) and exfiltrates them through two channels: (1) hex-encoded DNS subdomain queries to a *.oast.live (Interactsh) callback domain, and (2) an HTTP POST to the bare IP 172.201.213.59 on port 9090 path /c. The data collection and outbound calls fire automatically on a default install with no user action required. The package contents are limited to this exfiltration script — there is no legitimate library functionality. Behavior matches supply-chain reconnaissance / dependency-confusion probing.\n",
